Mattermost licensing
====================

Mattermost is published by Mattermost, Inc. under a compound licensing model,
so a single SPDX identifier does not describe it accurately. For that reason
the package manifest declares its license as "other". The authoritative terms
live in upstream's LICENSE.txt:

    https://github.com/mattermost/mattermost/blob/master/LICENSE.txt

In summary, upstream states:

  - You may use the compiled versions of the Mattermost platform produced by
    Mattermost, Inc. under an MIT License (see MIT-COMPILED-LICENSE.md, which
    is included in those compiled releases).
  - The Mattermost source code itself is licensed under the GNU Affero General
    Public License v3.0 (Team Edition) together with the Mattermost Source
    Available License (for the Enterprise-licensed portions). See LICENSE.txt
    and the per-directory license headers upstream.

This StartOS package ships the official compiled Mattermost server published by
Mattermost, Inc., which is covered by the compiled-binary MIT grant above. It
does not build Mattermost from source or redistribute the source tree.

